Name: Review of approved construction drawings and specifications
All drawings and specifications approved and up to date
Site access cleared and made safe
All personnel inducted; safety briefings completed
Dust, noise, and sediment barriers installed and functioning
Part 2 – Excavation and trenching (photos where applicable)
Subgrade proof rolled and natural ground conformant (ie. no excessive ground deformation)
Compaction testing performed on subgrade. 1x test per 2 layers per 40 linear meters
Trench depth and width comply with design
Set-out verified and matches IFC drawings
Trenches deeper than 1.5m require benching, or battering unless certified by a geotechnical engineer.
Pipes visually inspected for cracks and defects before installation
Material certs from manufacturer and visual inspection
Material to align with design drawings and load rating
No standing water or excessive moisture inside the trench.
Access and egress (ladders, steps) provided for trenches deeper than 1.2m
Access and egress for each trench.
Part 3 – Bedding & Pipe Installation (photos where applicable)
Correct bedding material used (sand, gravel, etc.)
Material complies with particle size, moisture content, MMDD
100mm thick bedding sand placed and screeded to correct heights for pipe placement
Correct pipe jointing method used (rubber ring, solvent weld, etc.)
Joints must be fully engaged and sealed per manufacturer specifications
Part 4 – Backfilling and compaction (photos where applicable)
Initial backfill material placed evenly around pipes
Backfill material placed evenly around haunches of pipes
Backfill in uniform layers of maximum 300mm thickness
Backfill shall be placed to a depth of 150mm minimum above collars of pipes or conduits
As-built levels and layout match design
Backfill layers compacted to minimum 93% MMDD
1x test per 2 layers per 40 linear meters.
RR-SEPD-BESS-FIC-004-01 - Proof roll
Prompting Name: ROBAR FIC | (insert material) | Proof roll Layer xx - RL xx.xxx

Name: 1.3 - Single pass with smooth drum roller to cover the area for the proof roll. If any doubts remain after a single pass, any subsequent passes, yet no greater than four, further compaction works shall be carried out till SEPD supervisor and PE are satisfied that there are no visual subgrade defects.
1.4 - The speed of the pass shall be constant and sufficient and no greater than walking speed.

1.5 - No proof rolling to be conducted within 2m of footings, foundations or retaining walls. Subject to a visual assessment and the principal’s approval, any compaction within this proximity of civil infrastructure shall be only achieved using hand compaction methods.
